<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2673389>
    dc:description "FIGURES 8–9. Morphological structures of Parascydmus corpusculum. Dorsal habitus of male (8); head, prothorax and elytral base in dorsal view (9). Abbreviations: abp, antebasal pit; bef, basal elytral fovea; lc, lateral carina." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2673389/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2673391>
    dc:description "FIGURES 10–11. Morphological structures of Parascydmus corpusculum. Head, prothorax and anterior portion of pterothorax in ventral view (10); pterothorax and abdomen in ventral view (11). Abbreviations: ar, anterior ridge; bst, basisternal portion of prosternum; gp, gular plate; gs, gular suture; hr, hypostomal ridge; lss, lateral suture of labium; mn, mentum; msvp, mesoventral intercoxal process; mt, mesal tooth; mtvp, metaventral intercoxal process; pcr, procoxal rest; pre, prepectus; smn, submentum." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2673391/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2673393>
    dc:description "FIGURES 12–14. Aedeagus of Parascydmus corpusculum in ventral (12) and lateral (13) views and original set of labels of lectotype (14)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2673393/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

